definition.value: This is an AE which is the movement of material from one point to another, such as a secreted chemical substance from a paranasal sinus cell .
This is an AE which might be beneficial in the management of sprue.
This is an AE which is disabling, deadly, and costly mental disorders that considerably impair physical health and disrupt psychosocial functioning.
This is an AE which is a mental disorder defined by abnormal eating behaviors that negatively affect a person's physical or mental health.

This is an AE which is a child's refusal to eat certain food groups, textures, solids or liquids for a period of at least one month, which causes the child to not gain enough weight, grow naturally or cause any developmental delays.

This is an AE which in infancy or early childhood, is a child's refusal to eat certain food groups, textures, solids or liquids for a period of at least one month, which causes the child to not gain enough weight, grow naturally or cause any developmental delays.[1] Feeding disorders resemble failure to thrive, except that at times in feeding disorder there is no medical or physiological condition that can explain the very small amount of food the children consume or their lack of growth.
This is an AE which is an abnormal immune response to food.
This is an AE which is acquired as a result of unpleasant experiences with foods represent a potent defense mechanism against poisoning.
This is an AE which is an intense desire to consume a specific food, and is different from normal hunger.
This is an AE which is a behavior where people or animals accumulate food.
This is an AE which is defined as alterations of pharmacokinetics or pharmacodynamics of a drug or nutritional element or a compromise in nutritional status as a result of the addition of a drug.

This is an AE which is a detrimental reaction, often delayed, to a food, beverage, food additive, or compound found in foods that produces symptoms in one or more body organs and systems, but generally refers to reactions other than food allergy.

This is an AE which is any illness resulting from the spoilage of contaminated food, pathogenic bacteria, viruses, or parasites that contaminate food, as well as prions (the agents of mad cow disease), and toxins such as aflatoxins in peanuts, poisonous mushrooms, and various species of beans that have not been boiled for at least 10 minutes.
This is an AE which is primarily associated with physical and ethical aspects and with end-of-life.
This is an AE which is a high-fat, adequate-protein, low-carbohydrate diet that in medicine is used mainly to treat hard-to-control (refractory) epilepsy in children.
This is an AE which refers an abnormal appetite for earth and other non-foods.
This is an AE which is a type of eating disorder in which people eat only within an extremely narrow repertoire of foods.
This is an AE which is a collection of pus that has built up within the tissue of the oral.
This is an AE which is a common side effect of various medical conditions which manifests as a reduced sense of oral touch or sensation, or a partial loss of sensitivity to sensory stimuli.
This is an AE which refers an unfavorable evolution of a disease, health condition or medical treatment  such as oral administration drug.

This is an AE which is a type of food allergy classified by a cluster of allergic reactions in the mouth and throat in response to eating certain (usually fresh) fruits, nuts, and vegetables that typically develops in adults with hay fever.
This is an AE which is a type of blister that forms when oral subdermal tissues and blood vessels are damaged without piercing the skin.

This is an AE which is a type of hematoma of tissue, the most common cause being capillaries damaged by trauma, causing oral localized bleeding that extravasates into the surrounding interstitial tissues.
This is an AE which is any medical condition that affects the oral integumentary system .
This is an AE which occurs when an organism's body oral  is invaded by pathogenic viruses,not verified in body] and infectious virus particles (virions) attach to and enter susceptible cells.
This is an AE which is a condition of abnormally high storage levels of vitamins, which can lead to various symptoms as over excitement, irritability, or even toxicity.

This is an AE which is a distortion of the sense of taste. Dysgeusia is also often associated with ageusia, which is the complete lack of taste, and hypogeusia, which is a decrease in taste sensitivity.
This is an AE which is a common, morbid, and costly malady, often complicated by otitis media, sinusitis, and asthma.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the mucous membranes caused by viral  that line the sinuses resulting in symptoms that may include thick nasal mucus, a plugged nose, and facial pain.

This is an AE which is usually precipitated by an earlier upper respiratory tract infection, generally of viral origin, mostly caused by rhinoviruses (with RVA and RVC giving more severe infection than RVB), coronaviruses, and influenza viruses, others caused by adenoviruses, human parainfluenza viruses, human respiratory syncytial virus, enteroviruses other than rhinoviruses, and metapneumovirus.
This is an AE which is a medical practice or technique of burning a part of a body  such as nose to remove or close off a part of it.

This is an AE which often manifests as nasal discharge with or without other nasal signs.
This is an AE which is determined by the nasal bones and the nasal cartilages, including the nasal septum which separates the nostrils and divides the nasal cavity into two.
This is an AE which is a viral nasal infection caused by the herpes virus.
This is an AE which causes a loss of olfactory sensory neurons (OSNs) and atrophy of the olfactory bulb (OB), which recovers when inflammation subsides.
This is an AE which caused by various traumas including blunt, and penetrating trauma and trauma caused by blast injury.

This is an AE which is a personal hygiene practice in which the nasal cavity is washed to flush out mucus and debris from the nose and sinuses, in order to enhance nasal breathing or can also refer to the use of saline nasal spray or nebulizers to moisten the mucous membranes.
